description: As of July 30, 2021, Vanguard ETF Series - Vanguard S&P 500 Index ETF has gone out of business. Vanguard ETF Series - Vanguard S&P 500 Index ETF is an exchange traded fund launched by Vanguard Investments Hong Kong Limited. It is managed by Vanguard Investments Australia Ltd. It invests in the public equity markets of the United States. The fund seeks to invest in the stocks of companies operating across diversified sectors. It invests in the stocks of large-cap companies. The fund seeks to replicate the performance of the S&P 500 Index, by investing in the stocks of companies as per their weightings in the index. Vanguard ETF Series - Vanguard S&P 500 Index ETF was formed on May 18, 2015 and is domiciled in Hong Kong.
name: Vanguard ETF Series - Vanguard S&P 500 Index ETF
